  "verbGlossary": {
    "PRECEDES": "First {target} must reach substantial completion before the second phase can begin production work; represents hard construction sequencing where physical work in one phase creates the substrate or access for the next",
    "GATES": "First {target} must achieve a defined milestone or approval before the second phase is authorized to start; represents a decision point, quality hold, or regulatory checkpoint that blocks downstream work",
    "FEEDS": "First {target} produces deliverables, information, or conditions that the second phase consumes as input; the phases may overlap in time but there is a directional dependency on outputs",
    "TRIGGERS": "Completion or {target} achievement in the first phase initiates the start of the second phase; represents a cause-and-effect relationship where one phase directly launches another",
    "ENABLES": "First {target} creates physical conditions or access that make the second phase feasible; without the first phase the second cannot proceed, but there is no formal gate or approval involved",
    "OVERLAPS": "Two {target}s execute concurrently with shared spatial or temporal constraints requiring active coordination; neither strictly precedes the other but they compete for the same space, access, or resources",
    "VALIDATES": "First {target} confirms that work completed in the second phase meets design intent, code requirements, or performance criteria; represents a verification or quality assurance relationship"
  }
